 font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">or</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">indeed </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> amount of carbon dioxide </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">that is said to contribute to it.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> It is well understood</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> that atmospheric CO</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:7.33pt; vertical-align:sub">2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> follows </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">(is </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">not </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">responsible for) </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">warming over historical</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> time-frames, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">but</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">acts </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">in reverse </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">–</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">atmospheric </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">carbon d</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ioxide </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">follow</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s warming,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">albeit </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">somewhat belatedly over-time. (</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">h</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">undreds</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> of years). This</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> trend points to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">gradual rise</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">temperature following the last Ice Age ~10k years ago</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and suggests we might be entering one of many interglacials </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">during</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> the current Ice Age.</span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> Interestingly researchers at Berkeley National Laboratory </span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">(Jan 2012) </span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">have </span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">found that </span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">newly discovered so-called Cr</span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">iegee biradicals molecules react to </span><span st